c: 3
v: 167
t: "And that He might mark out those who acted in hypocrisy: when they were told, \"Come and fight in God’s cause, or defend yourselves (actively, in order to keep the enemy outside the city),\" they said: \"If we but knew there would be fighting, we would indeed follow you.\" They that day were nearer to unbelief than to faith, uttering with their mouths what was not in their hearts. God knows very well what they were concealing"